SECTION 1: GRANT OF LICENSE (DUAL-LICENSE MODEL)

The Licensor (Himanshu) utilizes a Dual-License model to ensure this Backend
Software remains freely accessible for education and innovation, while
requiring fair compensation for commercial enterprise use.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1.1 NON-COMMERCIAL & EDUCATIONAL USE (FREE TIER)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Subject to full compliance with the Attribution Conditions, the Licensor
grants you a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive license to use, modify,
and deploy this Backend Software strictly for:

  ✅ PERSONAL PROJECTS & LEARNING
     Building sample projects, learning, local development, experimentation

  ✅ ACADEMIC & RESEARCH
     University projects, hackathons, thesis work, open-source contributions

  ✅ INTERNAL COMPANY USE (NON-REVENUE GENERATING)
     Using internally within a company for operations, NOT as commercial product

  ✅ NON-PROFIT ORGANIZATIONS
     Registered charities, NGOs where the platform is NOT monetized

CONDITIONS OF FREE TIER USE:
  • You must maintain all copyright headers in source code
  • You must not remove attribution from documentation
  • You must not use this to generate revenue
  • If you monetize, you MUST immediately obtain a Commercial License
  • You must allow audit verification of compliance

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1.2 COMMERCIAL USE RESTRICTION (PAID TIER REQUIRED)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

You may NOT use this Backend Software for Commercial Purposes under the Free
Tier. A valid, paid Commercial License is MANDATORY.

"COMMERCIAL PURPOSES" includes but is not limited to:

  ❌ Deploying a live marketplace that accepts transactions
  ❌ Use by any registered business entity
  ❌ Use by agencies/contractors building for paying clients
  ❌ Offering as SaaS or managed service
  ❌ Revenue generation: subscriptions, transaction fees, etc.
  ❌ Integrating into a commercial product or service

CLEAR RULE: If your organization has revenue and you deploy this Backend
Software, a Commercial License is required. No exceptions.

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1.3 OBTAINING A COMMERCIAL LICENSE
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

If you deploy this Backend Software for any Commercial Purpose, you MUST
obtain a Commercial License BEFORE deployment.

COMMERCIAL LICENSE COMPONENTS:
  ✓ Production deployment rights
  ✓ Tiered royalty model: 5% (₹0-₹50L) / 10% (₹50L+)
  ✓ Monthly revenue reporting & royalty payment
  ✓ Annual audit & compliance verification
  ✓ Source code attribution requirements
  ✓ Full legal documentation & formal agreement

DETAILED INFORMATION:
  → COMMERCIAL-LICENSE.md (complete terms)
  → COMMERCIAL-LICENSE-AGREEMENT.md (formal contract)

TO OBTAIN A LICENSE:
  📧 Email: hk8913114@gmail.com
  Subject: "Commercial License - [Company Name]"
  Include: Business name, registration number, expected revenue

PRICING & TERMS:
  • 5% monthly royalty for annual revenue ₹0-₹50 Lakhs
  • 10% monthly royalty for annual revenue ₹50 Lakhs+
  • Monthly reporting due by 15th of each month
  • Minimum 12-month term
  • No upfront setup fees

